{"ID":270287, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"287\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs286.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs288.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 287<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">above and on the earth beneath,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> the sun turned into darkness and the moon to blood,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> earthquakes\n  in divers places,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> the seas heaving beyond their bounds;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> then will appear one grand sign of the Son\n  of Man in heaven.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> But what will the world do? They will say it is a planet, a comet, etc. But the Son\n  of Man will come as the sign of the coming of the Son of Man,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> which will be as the light of the\n  morning cometh out of the east.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> (April 6, 1843.) DHC 5:336-337.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">On Leaving Meetings Near the Close<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">President Joseph Smith stated that the business of the conference had closed, and the remainder\n  would be devoted to instruction. It is an insult to a meeting for persons to leave just before its close.\n  If they must go out, let them go half an hour before. No gentlemen will go out of a meeting just as\n  closing. (April 7, 1843.) DHC 5:338-339.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">THE PROPHET EXPOUNDS THE SCRIPTURES<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Beasts of John&rsquo;s Revelation<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The subject I intend to speak upon this morning is one that I have seldom touched upon since\n  I commenced my ministry in the Church.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> It is a subject of great speculation, as well amongst the\n  elders of this Church, as among the divines of the day: it is in relation to the beasts spoken of by\n  John the Revelator.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> I have seldom spoken from the revelations; but as my subject is a constant\n  source of speculation amongst the elders, causing a division of sentiment<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and opinion in relation\n  to it, I now do it in order that division and differences of opinion may be done away with, and not\n  that correct knowledge on the subject is so much needed at the present time.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">It is not very essential for the elders to have knowledge in relation to the meaning of beasts, and\n  heads and horns,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and other figures made use of in the revelations; still, it may be necessary, to\n  prevent contention<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> and division and do away with suspense. If we get puffed up<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> by thinking that\n  we have much knowledge,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> we are apt to get a contentious spirit,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and correct knowledge is\n  necessary to cast out that spirit.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Punishment of Suspense<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The evil of being puffed up with correct (though useless) knowledge is not so great as the evil\n  of contention.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> Knowl-<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113527\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113527)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113527)\">D&amp;C 29:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113854\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113854)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113854)\">D&amp;C 45:40<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107621\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107621)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107621)\">Joel 2:31<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110739\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=